The morphology of the H10P10000NPs was observed by TEM. As disclosed in Fig. 2A, H10P10000NPs were quasi-spherical nanoparticles with the average size of 59.5 ± 17.4 nm (Fig. 2A inset, based on counting 100 particles). The H10P10000NPs in water were light-yellow in the bright field and emitted green fluorescence under 365 nm UV-light (Fig. 2B inset) with the maximum excitation wavelength (
λ ex max
) of 440 nm and maximum emission wavelength (
λ ex max
) of 520 nm.
